    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense faces a favorable slate today, headlined by a high-upside core led by **Kyle Tucker** (77.10) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.92). **Tucker** remains an elite play against Landen Roupp despite the rain risk; his consistent xwOBA and the favorable wind conditions outweigh the weather concerns. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a soft matchup against Jack Kochanowicz, with the SP\u2019s poor xERA (5.35) providing the necessary cushion for a massive day. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) is our standout middle-infield play; his dynamic platoon edge against Reynaldo L\u00f3pez, coupled with the high scoring environment against a weak starter, makes him an essential start today.\n\nWe are hunting stolen bases, but the optimizer prioritized pure offensive efficiency in the utility and outfield slots. **Jackson Merrill** (70.77) earns a spot thanks to a massive 14% park factor boost and a favorable platoon matchup against Jimmy Herget. The most difficult exclusion was **Marcell Ozuna** (53.80), who narrowly missed the cut. While his projected output is solid, the optimizer favored the higher volatility and matchup-specific advantages of **Andy Pages** (62.83) and **Brady House** (63.81). The matchup against Reynaldo L\u00f3pez is so exploitable that **Nasim Nunez** (62.09) was also locked in, as his speed and the massive SP skill differential make him an undervalued contributor to our SB pursuit.\n\nManagement must remain vigilant regarding the 35% rain risk impacting **Kyle Tucker** and **Andy Pages**. Furthermore, all lineups are currently pending; should **Gunnar Henderson** or **Luis Robert Jr.** experience a drop in batting order priority, their scores\u2014already hampered by high-level hold pitchers\u2014could plummet further, potentially necessitating a pivot to **Jacob Wilson** or **Coby Mayo** if they find themselves in favorable spots. We will monitor the status of **Drake Baldwin**, whose score of 48.67 is marginal, and ensure that our lineup depth remains capable of absorbing any late-scratch adjustments.",
